00:00:15,307 --> 00:00:17,643
<i>My name is Jackson Norris.</i>

3
00:00:17,727 --> 00:00:20,396
<i>Today will be the most important
of my career.</i>

4
00:00:20,480 --> 00:00:23,983
<i>My final interview with
the most infamous prisoner in America.</i>

5
00:00:25,193 --> 00:00:28,780
<i>A man that the world thought was
a terrorist called the Mandarin.</i>

6
00:00:28,862 --> 00:00:31,783
<i>But is now alleged to be nothing
but an actor.</i>

7
00:00:32,616 --> 00:00:35,369
<i>Thus far, the subject has been evasive</i>

8
00:00:35,453 --> 00:00:38,456
<i>and apparently oblivious
to the point of my work.</i>

9
00:00:38,664 --> 00:00:41,667
<i>In fact, he seems oblivious
to pretty much everything.</i>

10
00:00:42,460 --> 00:00:44,337
<i>Except his own growing celebrity.</i>

11
00:00:44,420 --> 00:00:46,046
INMATE: Here he comes.
Here he comes.

12
00:00:46,130 --> 00:00:48,966
<i>JACKSON: Because now
the whole world knows his name.</i>

13
00:00:49,049 --> 00:00:50,468
INMATES: (CHANTING)
Trevor! Trevor! Trevor!

14
00:00:50,801 --> 00:00:54,680
<i>JACKSON: This is my last chance to get
beyond his lies and excuses,</i>

15
00:00:54,764 --> 00:00:58,058
<i>to confront the subject
with elements of his own past</i>

16
00:00:58,142 --> 00:00:59,978
<i>in order to unlock the truth.</i>

17
00:01:00,645 --> 00:01:04,022
<i>Because we need to know,
once and for all,</i>

18
00:01:04,106 --> 00:01:06,775
<i>who is Trevor Slattery?</i>

19
00:01:18,787 --> 00:01:21,915
Bloody hell.
It's not exactly The Ritz, is it?

20
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:24,418
Hey, stop right there.

21
00:01:24,543 --> 00:01:26,754
-(GRUNTS) Hey!
-(CLATTERING)

22
00:01:27,212 --> 00:01:29,507
Come on, Mr. Slattery,
you know you supposed to wait for me.

23
00:01:29,591 --> 00:01:32,218
Lunchtime ain't safe around here
for a celebrity like yourself.

24
00:01:32,301 --> 00:01:35,263
So, Herman, with whom
shall we lunch today?

25
00:01:35,430 --> 00:01:38,932
Serial killers? Nonces?
I hear the Triads are a good giggle.

26
00:01:39,016 --> 00:01:40,977
HERMAN: Now remember, sir,
you have that 3:00 with Mr. Norris.

27
00:01:41,060 --> 00:01:44,271
If only my mother could see me
in my very own documentary.

28
00:01:44,354 --> 00:01:46,566
I still think you should've done
that exclusive with 60 Minutes.

29
00:01:46,649 --> 00:01:49,067
I told you. I'll never work for CBS again.

30
00:01:49,152 --> 00:01:51,612
Wait. Herman, where's my choccy milk?

31
00:01:51,695 --> 00:01:53,364
I'm so sorry, sir. I'll be right back.

32
00:01:53,781 --> 00:01:56,700
And while you're there can you see
if they've got any kale?

33
